children.name: Scene 3: Hyperloop Journey Layout: - A top navbar should be present with the game title on the left and a progress bar on the right indicating the distance traveled. - The player's view is now inside a virtual pod traveling through a transparent Hyperloop tube. - A simplified landscape of South Africa (mountains, plains, etc.) should be displayed outside the tube, creating a sense of speed. - A Heads-Up Display (HUD) element should be positioned at the bottom showing travel speed, estimated arrival time, and a progress bar indicating distance traveled. - The HUD should also display the current score and any power-ups that the player has collected. - A button for pausing the game should be present on the HUD. Visuals: - The Hyperloop tube should be a simple cylinder with a transparent material. - The landscape outside the tube can be a low-polygon 3D model with basic textures. - The HUD elements should be clear and easy to understand. Use icons or text labels for speed and estimated arrival time. The progress bar can be a colored bar that fills up as the journey progresses. - The score and power-ups should be displayed using simple icons. - The pause button should be easily identifiable using a contrasting color or hover effect. Scene 4: Educational Prompts Layout: - This scene reuses the Hyperloop Journey layout (Scene 3). - Text overlays should appear on the HUD highlighting benefits of Hyperloop. - The HUD should also display the current score and any power-ups that the player has collected. - A button for pausing the game should be present on the HUD. Visuals: - Maintain the visuals from Scene 3. - Text overlays can fade in and out at specific points during the journey. Use contrasting colors or animations to make them stand out. Consider short icons or visuals alongside the text to reinforce the message (e.g., a clock icon for "Reduced Travel Time"). - The score and power-ups should be displayed using simple icons. - The pause button should be easily identifiable using a contrasting color or hover effect.

Visuals: - Use a clean and futuristic design aesthetic. - The map can be a flat plane with glowing city icons. - Control panels can be simple rectangles with rounded corners and placeholder icons for buttons and levers. - Title card text should be bold and easy to read. - Buttons in the control panels should have a 3D effect to make them look interactive. - The bottom navbar should have a dark background with white text for better visibility. Instructions: 1. The top title card should be centered and have a font size of at least 36px. The font should be bold and easy to read. 2. The central area showcasing the holographic map should take up most of the screen. The map should be a flat plane with glowing city icons. The cities should be highlighted with a bright color to make them stand out. 3. The control panels should be arranged around the map. They should be simple rectangles with rounded corners and placeholder icons for buttons and levers. The buttons should have a 3D effect to make them look interactive. The control panels should be evenly spaced around the map. 4. The bottom navbar should have a dark background with white text for better visibility. The Restart and Exit buttons should be clearly labeled and easily identifiable. The buttons should be placed at the center of the navbar and have a 3D effect to make them look interactive. 5. The overall design should have a clean and futuristic aesthetic. The colors used should be bright and contrasting to make the design more visually appealing.

Text Labels: Text labels should be positioned above each cargo pod. The labels should indicate the cargo type and destination city. The labels should be clear and readable. The font size should be large enough to be easily readable but not too large as to clutter the scene. 4. Footer: The footer should contain buttons for "Restart" and "Exit". The buttons should be easily identifiable using contrasting colors or hover effects. The buttons should be positioned at the bottom of the scene. 5. children.name: Design for "Destination City Arrival": Layout: - The top section of the screen should display the game title "Hyperloop SA" and a button to return to the Control Center. - The center section of the screen should display a background image or a simple landmark of the destination city. - The bottom section of the screen should display a point summary screen with three categories: speed, safety, and on-time delivery. Each category should have an icon, a label, and a numerical value indicating the points earned. - Two buttons should be displayed at the bottom of the screen: "Restart" and "Exit". The "Restart" button should reset the game and take the player back to the Control Center. The "Exit" button should close the game and return the player to the main menu. Visuals: - The design aesthetic should be consistent with the previous scenes, using a clean and futuristic style. - The game title should be displayed in bold and easy-to-read text. - The background image or landmark should be relevant to the destination city and visually appealing. - The point summary screen should use icons and labels to clearly indicate the points earned in each category. - The buttons should be easily identifiable using contrasting colors or hover effects. The "Restart" button should be green and the "Exit" button should be red. Overall, the design should provide a clear and informative summary of the player's performance in the game and offer easy navigation options to restart or exit the game.
